column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Dabargar would have you avenge a fallen friend.
Speak with the Yok Huy guide.
Slay the beasts at the Shades of Grief.
Speak with the Yok Huy guide.
Speak with Dabargar.
Ah, the hero who brought low Valigarmanda. I would beg your aid in exterminating a new threat that has visited the Yok Huy.
One of our kin recently went missing, only to turn up just outside the ruins at the Shades of Grief...reduced to a desiccated corpse.
Judging from the wounds, the poor soul must have been fed upon by a particularly formidable bloodsucker. This fiend cannot be suffered to live!
To lure it out, we have placed blood-soaked meat at strategic locations around the ruins. One of my comrades is there now, and he'd doubtless be grateful for your assistance.
You'll find the Shades of Grief down the road to the northwest. Would you meet with my comrade and check on the trap we've laid?
Gee hee hee... Ahem! Greetings, visitor!
You know the plan, yes? Well, there's a problem. Some <Emphasis>other</Emphasis> creatures have been drawn in by the smell of the meat, oh yes!
Yes, that despicable bloodsucker will never creep out from hiding so long as they're around! Yes, I'm afraid I must ask you to get rid of them!
Luckily, there is nothing our quarry loves better than fresh blood. The more of it, the better, oh yes!
I'll watch from a distance, yes? Once the creatures have been dealt with, come to the west side of the ruins. Hee hee...kee hee hee!
Gee hee hee! Finally. You must be so exhausted after all that dashing and slashing. As for me, I feel rather invigorated, oh yes!
Why, I was practically counting the seconds...until I could drain your life's blood!
The enemy reveals itself!
The bloodsucker was disguised as my comrade all along!? Surely that cannot be!
F-Forgive me, I know not what to say. If the fiend was possessed of such an alarming ability, I should think someone would have made mention of it before now!
Years ago, the Head of Reason once speculated that the beasts we call bloodsuckers are in fact beings known as “voidsent,” come from another realm.
Others have even suggested they might be invaders from distant stars! I have heard many and more theories over the years, but perhaps I was unwise to shrug them off as I have.
In any case, the threat is no more, and our village owes you a debt. Now, if you will excuse me, I must find my missing comrade!
